Tracker
description:
Does the tracking for all applications (currently Net Metrix, Google Analytics, Chartbeat).

For tracking Net Metrix make sure the host under which the page is requested is configured
as live host in `./app/node_modules/tracking/config.json`.
If the host is not whitelisted tracking is logged to `console`.

name: trackPageView
description:
Tracks page views.

Net Metrix:
Tracks Net Metrix or logs tracking to `console` for non-live hosts.

params.name: data.domain
params.description: The identifier for the Audit. For "Nordwestschweiz Netz" this is `'aznetz'`.

params.name: data.path
params.description: The path information object. This object is used to construct additional sections in Net Metrix tags.

params.name: data.path.path
params.description: The path of the url of the current page.

params.name: data.path.view
params.description:
The view.
                                          For pageview tracking, e.g. `path.event=='pageview'`: `page` or `'page-noscript'` (when JavaScript disabled).
                                          For event tracking, e.g. `path.event!='pageview'`: `'[name of the component that receives the user event]'`.

params.name: data.path.event
params.description: The user generated event. `'pageview'` for page view tracking or `'[name of event]'`.

params.name: data.path.id
params.description: The ID of the data or the component or the page displayed. Use this field if you want to specify something such as am ID of a video or a keyword of a search.

params.name: data.path.paging
params.description: The paging information. Example: For the image gallery this is the index of the image requested.

params.name: data.screenWidth
params.description: The width of the devices' screen in pixels.

params.name: data.screenHeight
params.description: The height of the devices' screen in pixels.

name: getNetMetrixTag
description: Gets the Net Metrix tag to track.

return.description: The Net Metrix tag as string.

name: isNetMetrixLiveHost
description: Determines if the current host is a live host which has to be tracked in Net Metrix.

return.description: Returns `true` if the current host is a live host.
